<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
</div>
<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="ib8kt">There are several different types of investment accounts to get started with. If you prefer a hands-off approach, you can open an account with a robo-advisor that will create an appropriate portfolio for you automatically. You can open a standard brokerage account to invests in stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and ETFs. Or, you can open a retirement account like an IRA to invest in those things, which could give you some big tax advantages.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="qna">
<div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<p data-block-key="lhkj0">What is good to invest in with $100?</p>
<svg class="collapsed-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
</div>
<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="qkopg">If you&#x27;re starting with $100 or a similar amount of money, there are some good choices for you. You could use a robo-advisor to start an automated investment account and add to it periodically. You can open a brokerage account and invest in an index fund. And with more brokers offering fractional share investing, you can even create a portfolio of individual stocks with a $100 initial investment.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="qna">
<div class="flex items-center justify-between py-24 border-b border-gray-400 qna-header hub-faq">
<p data-block-key="lhkj0">What is the No. 1 thing to invest in?</p>
<svg class="collapsed-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-down</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M151.5 347.8L3.5 201c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l19.8-19.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0L160 282.7l119.7-118.5c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0l19.8 19.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-148 146.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0z"></path>
</svg>
<svg class="expanded-icon w-24px h-24px ml-4px" viewBox="0 0 320 512">
<title>angle-up</title>
<path fill="currentColor" d="M168.5 164.2l148 146.8c4.7 4.7 4.7 12.3 0 17l-19.8 19.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L160 229.3 40.3 347.8c-4.7 4.7-12.3 4.7-17 0L3.5 328c-4.7-4.7-4.7-12.3 0-17l148-146.8c4.7-4.7 12.3-4.7 17 0z"></path>
</svg>
</div>
<div class="qna-content">
<p data-block-key="qkopg">This depends on your particular goals, risk tolerance, and available capital. For example, there&#x27;s a solid argument to be made that buying simple S&amp;P 500 index funds is the best investment for most people, but there&#x27;s also an argument to be made in favor of individual stocks for investors with the time and desire to research their investment choices.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
